Interface ComponentAddonFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AutoFocusJobFactory, BrentFocusSearchAddonFactory, CellDetectionJobAddonFactory, CellXAddonFactory, ChangePositionJobAddonFactory, ComponentAddonFactoryAdapter, ComposedImagingJobAddonFactory, CompositeJobAddonFactory, ContinuousImagingJobFactory, ControllerJobAddonFactory, CustomJobAddonFactory, DefaultObserverFactory, DeviceJobAddonFactory, DeviceSlidesJobAddonFactory, DropletMicrofluidicJobAddonFactory, EvaporationControllerFactory, ExhaustiveFocusSearchAddonFactory, FlexibleControllerFactory, FluigentJobAddonFactory, FocusingJobAddonFactory, GlowVisualizerAddonFactory, ImagingJobAddonFactory, LabelVisualizerAddonFactory, LiveModifiableJobAddonFactory, MatlabScoresAddonFactory, MicroplateJobAddonFactory, NemesysJobAddonFactory, OnixJobAddonFactory, OnOffDeviceJobAddonFactory, OscillatingDeviceJobAddonFactory, OutOfFocusJobAddonFactory, ParallelImagingJobAddonFactory, PlateScanningJobAddonFactory, QuickDetectAddonFactory, RepeatJobAddonFactory, ScriptingJobAddonFactory, SimpleScoresAddonFactory, SlimJobAddonFactory, StaggeringJobAddonFactory, StandardSaveSettingsFactory, StatisticsJobAddonFactory, TableControllerFactory, WaitForUserJobAddonFactory, WaitJobAddonFactory, ZSlidesJobAddonFactory

    public interface ComponentAddonFactory
    General interface for all addons which create and provide a UI for the configuration of a measurement components. See ComponentAddonFactoryAdapter for an adapter class to simplify implementation.
    Author:
    Moritz Lang

    • Method Detail

      • createComponent

        Component createComponent(PositionInformation positionInformation,
                          Configuration configuration,
                          ConstructionContext constructionContext)
                   throws ConfigurationException,
                          AddonException
        Creates an addon for the given configuration. Throws a construction addon exception if the configuration type provided is not supported.
        Parameters:
        positionInformation - The position in the measurement hierarchy where the addon should be constructed.
        configuration - The configuration of the addon.
        constructionContext - The context of the construction, providing information and functionality in the construction of the addon.
        Returns:
        The constructed addon.
        Throws:
        ConfigurationException - Thrown if the configuration is invalid.
        AddonException - Thrown if an error occurred during the construction.

      • createComponentUI

        ComponentAddonUI<?> createComponentUI(java.lang.String typeIdentifier,
                                      YouScopeClient client,
                                      YouScopeServer server)
                               throws AddonException
        Returns a new UI to configure a component of the given type identifier.
        Parameters:
        typeIdentifier - The ID for which a configuration addon should be created.
        client - Interface to allow the addon to communicate with the client.
        server - Interface to the server.
        Returns:
        The created addon for a given configuration type.
        Throws:
        AddonException - Thrown if configuration type identifier is not supported by this factory, or if any general error occured during the configuration addon creation.

      • getSupportedTypeIdentifiers

        java.lang.String[] getSupportedTypeIdentifiers()
        Returns a list of all component type identifiers supported by this factory. A type identifier is a string unique for a given component type, with which the component type is identified.
        Returns:
        List of supported component types.

      • isSupportingTypeIdentifier

        boolean isSupportingTypeIdentifier(java.lang.String typeIdentifier)
        Returns true if this factory supports configurations with the given ID, false otherwise.
        Parameters:
        typeIdentifier - The ID of the configuration for which it should be queried if this factory supports its construction.
        Returns:
        True if this factory supports creating configurations with the given ID, false otherwise.

      • getComponentMetadata

        ComponentMetadata<?> getComponentMetadata(java.lang.String typeIdentifier)
                                   throws AddonException
        Returns the metadata (like human readable name) for a given configuration type.
        Parameters:
        typeIdentifier - The type identifier of the configuration for which the metadata should be returned.
        Returns:
        The metadata of the given configuration.
        Throws:
        AddonException - Thrown if identifier is not supported by the addon.
